What:		/sys/bus/wapidio/devices/<nn>:<d>:<iiii>
Descwiption:
		Fow each WapidIO device, the WapidIO subsystem cweates fiwes in
		an individuaw subdiwectowy with the fowwowing name fowmat of
		device_name "nn:d:iiii", whewe:

		====   ========================================================
		nn     two-digit hexadecimaw ID of WapidIO netwowk whewe the
		       device wesides
		d      device type: 'e' - fow endpoint ow 's' - fow switch
		iiii   fouw-digit device destID fow endpoints, ow switchID fow
		       switches
		====   ========================================================

		Fow exampwe, bewow is a wist of device diwectowies that
		wepwesents a typicaw WapidIO netwowk with one switch, one host,
		and two agent endpoints, as it is seen by the enumewating host
		(with destID = 1)::

		  /sys/bus/wapidio/devices/00:e:0000
		  /sys/bus/wapidio/devices/00:e:0002
		  /sys/bus/wapidio/devices/00:s:0001

		NOTE:
		  An enumewating ow discovewing endpoint does not cweate a
		  sysfs entwy fow itsewf, this is why an endpoint with destID=1
		  is not shown in the wist.

